We want to target the journey image.

00:02:06.110 --> 00:02:11.810
We can add a background image in CSS with the background property,

00:02:11.810 --> 00:02:16.805
then we use a URL to provide a link to the file location.

00:02:16.805 --> 00:02:25.080
This is stored within the images folder and the image is called backgrounds dot JPEG.

00:02:25.600 --> 00:02:30.470
Of course if yours is named something different you'll need to change that.

00:02:30.470 --> 00:02:35.890
Then we're going to add some properties first of all, of no repeats.

00:02:36.530 --> 00:02:41.390
By default, images will be repeated horizontally and vertically.

00:02:41.390 --> 00:02:46.490
We add no repeat because we want just one full-size image.

00:02:46.490 --> 00:02:50.275
Then center sensor.

00:02:50.275 --> 00:02:53.270
This will sensor the image on both the X and

00:02:53.270 --> 00:02:57.815
the Y axis by default to replace in the top-left.

00:02:57.815 --> 00:03:01.250
This moves the image back into the center.

00:03:01.250 --> 00:03:04.945
Then finally we're going to add fixed onto the end,

00:03:04.945 --> 00:03:07.310
this keeps the image position fixed when we

00:03:07.310 --> 00:03:11.380
scroll and we'll take a look at these in just a moment.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:17.240
Give that a save, then if we go over to the browser and then refresh,

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:21.475
we still see that no image has been displayed on the screen.

00:03:21.475 --> 00:03:24.140
This is because the background image will only be

00:03:24.140 --> 00:03:27.080
the height of the content inside of this div,

00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:28.885
which is the text,

00:03:28.885 --> 00:03:33.545
and this text however hides the image because of the gray background.

00:03:33.545 --> 00:03:40.230
If we temporarily go over to the style and remove the background,

00:03:42.050 --> 00:03:45.830
cut out and save and then refresh.

00:03:45.830 --> 00:03:50.520
We can see that the background has just about appeared on the screen.

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:53.635
Let's add this back in.

00:03:53.635 --> 00:03:57.455
To get around this, we can set the height of the journey image

00:03:57.455 --> 00:04:01.480
in the CSS using the minimum high property,

00:04:01.480 --> 00:04:05.100
and we can add this just below the background property.

00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:09.075
To scroll back down to the journey image,

00:04:09.075 --> 00:04:17.505
and then we can add the minimum height of 100 vh.

00:04:17.505 --> 00:04:20.585
Minimum height can be a pixel value,

00:04:20.585 --> 00:04:24.815
a percentage, or by 70 to 100 vh.

00:04:24.815 --> 00:04:28.790
This set says to be 100 percent of the viewport height.

00:04:28.790 --> 00:04:32.615
The viewport is a visible screen of the device.

00:04:32.615 --> 00:04:35.855
Save that, and now if we refresh,

00:04:35.855 --> 00:04:39.515
we now see that the image is on the screen.

00:04:39.515 --> 00:04:42.545
One thing to notice when scrolling down in the browser,

00:04:42.545 --> 00:04:45.380
that the image is in a fixed position.

00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:48.380
This is because we set this to be fixed.

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:51.530
If we were to remove this, we can see by

00:04:51.530 --> 00:04:55.340
refreshing the browser that the image scrolls with the rest of the page,

00:04:55.340 --> 00:04:59.130
but I want to keep mine fixed as I like to look at this.

